@ecosse3 If you need/want to keep neovim _really_ up-to-date, I'd recommend just cloning the repo and building from source. Just `make; sudo make install` should work fine. (It's also much faster since you don't have to recompile _everything_, including dependencies, from scratch each time.)

(And if you want to keep using homebrew, `brew install --HEAD --build-from-source luajit;
brew install --HEAD --build-from-source neovim` as mentioned in the pinned issue successfully builds the latest commit.)
